descript.abstract: Europe Water contains other rivers/lakes for Europe.
descript.purpose: Europe Water provides a base map layer of water for Europe not contained in Europe Major Water. To display all water for Europe, use this data set in conjunction with Europe Major Water.
descript.supplinf: Largest scale when displaying the data: 1:25,000.

procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by ESRI: Extracted Eur_maj_w.shp and Eur_min_w.shp from AND Global Road Data and merged them into one shapefile. Removed all administrative boundary lines within large water features. Removed the Caspian Sea, which was incomplete. Recoded some features for consistency. Removed three large land polygons miscoded as water. Added CNTRYNAME attribute from Europe Countries. Added and coded SQKM attribute. Recoded features, named for the province they reside in, as blank. Added and coded the RANK attribute. Recoded the TYPE attribute with the type descriptions. Removed unneeded attributes. Renamed and rearranged attributes as needed. Created ArcGIS® layer file (.lyr), projection file (.prj), and spatial indices. Converted the data set to SDC.

dataqual.logic: No duplicate features are present. The shapefile is converted to SDC (Smart Data Compression) format in ArcSDE®. This verifies and validates the geometry.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.
